ic): habitational name for someone from Budy, the name of a village in Ukraine and another in Belarus.","Slovenian and Croatian: from the personal name <i>Budin</i>, a short form of (Old) Slavic compound names based on the element <i>bud</i> ‘to inspire’ (from <i>buditi</i>), as for example <i>Budislav</i> ‘inspiring glory’."]}]},{"name":"Fergus","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Anglicized form of Fearghas , one of the Gaelic names that has recently also been favoured by parents without Irish or Scottish connections."],"variants":[{"name":"Fearghas","meanings":["From Irish <i>fear</i> ‘man’ + <i>gus</i> ‘vigour’; the name of a shadowy hero in Irish mythology, also of the grandfather of St Columba."]}]},{"name":"Colban","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Irish: Colman, a pigeon"],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Fergus Colban Buchan 4th Earl of Buchan was born in 1165, in Stirlingshire, Scotland as the son of Roger Buchan 3rd Earl  of Buchan. He had at least 1 daughter. He died in 1199, in Scotland, at the age of 34, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"1165–1199":"1165–1199","1184–1244":"1184–1244","1145–1179":"1145–1179","1179":"1179","1145":"1145","1244":"1244","1199":"1199","1165":"1165","1184":"1184","Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1165–1199":"1165–1199","1184–1244":"1184–1244","1145–1179":"1145–1179","1179":"1179","1145":"1145","1244":"1244","1199":"1199","1165":"1165","1184":"1184","Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Stirlingshire, Scotland":"Stirlingshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1165–1199":"1165–1199","1184–1244":"1184–1244","1145–1179":"1145–1179","1179":"1179","1145":"1145","1244":"1244","1199":"1199","1165":"1165","1184":"1184","Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Buchan, Aberdeenshire, Écosse","Scotland":"Écosse",